Container : pre-written program, it provides the below features

Lifecycle management
Declarative services (Transaction, Security, Logging, Profyling etc.,)

Servlet Container : Tomcat
EJB Container : weblogic, jboss, websphere
POJO container : Spring


Data Layer:

JDBC
Hibernate (Framework)-> JDBC
JPA (Specification) -> Hibernate / Toplink ->JDBC



@SpringBootApplication
|
@Configuration : It will scan for the configuration beans  annotated with @Bean  (RestTemplate, MessageSource, Docket etc.,)
@ComponentScan :  It will scan for stero-type annotations (@Controller/@RestController, @Service, @Repository, @Component)
@EnableAutoConfiguration : 
Spring-Boot-Starter-Web  : @EnableWebMvc
Spring-Boot-Starter-Jms : @EnableJms 
Spring-Boot-Starter-Secutiry : @EnableWebSecurity 



OOAD - OCP (Open-Close Prinicple)

Close for modification, Open for extension (Decorator)

